In order to add an entry to the DB, use the command

python export_to_db.py -i args.ini -d

-d is for dry mode, remove it to add the entry


Two options for the args.ini file :


########
### 1) From the flow path, recommanded.
########

[SALON]
flow_path=flow_lumi
t2_path=
t3_path=
t4_path=
t5_path=
name= SALON
computation_tag= test
additional_tag= UCR4C4
credentials_path= /gpfs/projects/acad/leds/DataBase_examples/.credentials.yaml
bulk_prim_stru=SALON.cif
database= phosphors
collection= test_collection


########
### 2) with the full path to the 4 points. No medata from the relax files stored in that case
########

[SALON]
flow_path=
t2_path=/gpfs/projects/acad/leds/DataBase_examples/adding_entry_to_DB/flow_lumi/w0/t2/outdata/out_GSR.nc  
t3_path=/gpfs/projects/acad/leds/DataBase_examples/adding_entry_to_DB/flow_lumi/w0/t3/outdata/out_GSR.nc
t4_path=/gpfs/projects/acad/leds/DataBase_examples/adding_entry_to_DB/flow_lumi/w0/t4/outdata/out_GSR.nc
t5_path=/gpfs/projects/acad/leds/DataBase_examples/adding_entry_to_DB/flow_lumi/w0/t5/outdata/out_GSR.nc
name= SALON
computation_tag= test
additional_tag= UCR4C4
credentials_path= /gpfs/projects/acad/leds/DataBase_examples/.credentials.yaml
bulk_prim_stru=SALON.cif
database= phosphors
collection= test_collection


########
For the two cases, if the bulk structure is not available, leave the argument empty:
#########


[SALON]
flow_path=
t2_path=/gpfs/projects/acad/leds/DataBase_examples/adding_entry_to_DB/flow_lumi/w0/t2/outdata/out_GSR.nc
t3_path=/gpfs/projects/acad/leds/DataBase_examples/adding_entry_to_DB/flow_lumi/w0/t3/outdata/out_GSR.nc
t4_path=/gpfs/projects/acad/leds/DataBase_examples/adding_entry_to_DB/flow_lumi/w0/t4/outdata/out_GSR.nc
t5_path=/gpfs/projects/acad/leds/DataBase_examples/adding_entry_to_DB/flow_lumi/w0/t5/outdata/out_GSR.nc
name= SALON
computation_tag= test
additional_tag= UCR4C4
credentials_path= /gpfs/projects/acad/leds/DataBase_examples/.credentials.yaml
bulk_prim_stru=
database= phosphors
collection= test_collection

